The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, March 22, 2004 				 Capturing India with the lens
Photography as a form of art has bewitched man ever since the invention of the camera lens that could capture infinitismal fragments of life and preserve them for posterity. Fujifilm  Capturing the spirit of life with the lens is a unique photo exhibition that celebrates the art of photography. On display at the ongoing exhibition is a select collection of photographs, captured on Fujifilm, by the renowned Fujifilm Super Six Photographers. This elite group of artists includes Rajesh Bedi with his collection on Wildlife, Prabuddha Dasgupta with Fashion, Avinash Pasrichas compilation on Dance, Pradeep Mandhani with his album on Cricket, Ashok Dilwalis collected photographs on Nature and Prakash Dubey with his shots of the Creative, of which The Wings of Commitment is featured above. The exhibition is aimed at promoting the art of photography as a hobby among its enthusiasts and judging by the breathtaking assortment on display, it is all set to be a winner.																								Event: An exhibition of photographs																								When: Till March 27; 3 pm - 8 pm																								Where: Academy of Fine Arts
